href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is said to be <fr:em><fr:strong>enumerable</fr:strong></fr:em> whenever there exists a surjection <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A]]></fr:tex>, referred to as an <fr:em><fr:strong>enumeration</fr:strong></fr:em>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:p>In an <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumeration</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A]]></fr:tex> of a set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, we think of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> as a “code” for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex> when <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}}=a]]></fr:tex>; these “codes” are not unique unless <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KR.xml"
addr="jms-00KR"
title="Bijection">bijection</fr:link>. By virtue of the viewpoint of quotients as surjections developed in <fr:ref
addr="jms-00MB"
taxon="Example" />, <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumerability</fr:link> expresses when a given set can be built up from the natural numbers by quotienting (i.e. identifying codes that are taken to the same element by the <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumeration</fr:link>).</fr:p><fr:tree
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3721</fr:anchor><fr:addr>jms-00MH</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00MH.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Countable set</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
