expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3726</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#375</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-375.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00MI</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Suppose that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00MH.xml"
addr="jms-00MH"
title="Countable set">countable</fr:link>. We must find a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A+{\mathopen {}\left  [1\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>; if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is empty, this is the same as to find a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\to {\mathopen {}\left  [1\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, which we have by <fr:ref
addr="jms-00MA"
taxon="Example" />. On the other hand, if we have an enumeration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow {A}]]></fr:tex>, we may define an enumeration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e'\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A+{\mathopen {}\left  [1\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   \begin {aligned}   e'{\mathopen {}\left (0\right )\mathclose {}} &= 0\\   e'{\mathopen {}\left (n+1\right )\mathclose {}} &= e{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}}   \end {aligned}  ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Conversely, suppose that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A+{\mathopen {}\left  [1\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumerable</fr:link> by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A+{\mathopen {}\left  [1\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is empty, we are done. If to the contrary <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is inhabited by some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a_0]]></fr:tex>, we let define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e'\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A]]></fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[   e'{\mathopen {}\left (i\right )\mathclose {}} =   \begin {cases}    e{\mathopen {}\left (i\right )\mathclose {}} &\text {when } e{\mathopen {}\left (i\right )\mathclose {}}\in  A\\    a_0 &\text {otherwise}   \end {cases}  ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
