expanded="true"
root="false"
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3821</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#365</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-365.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00NJ</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Of course, as <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is non-empty, it is enough to show that it is not <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumerable</fr:link>. We know that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {R}\cong  {\mathopen {}\left  [0,1\right  ]\mathclose {}}\cong  {\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {N}\to {\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}\cong  \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {N}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, and and it follows from <fr:ref
addr="jms-00NF"
taxon="Theorem" /> that the latter is not <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumerable</fr:link>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
