xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>3739</fr:anchor><fr:addr>#373</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-373.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>29</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
type="local"
href="jonmsterling.xml"
addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00ML</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00MH.xml"
addr="jms-00MH"
title="Countable set">countable</fr:link> sets. If either <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is empty, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  B]]></fr:tex> is empty and thus <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00MH.xml"
addr="jms-00MH"
title="Countable set">countable</fr:link>. Otherwise, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_A\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_B\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  B]]></fr:tex> be <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00ME.xml"
addr="jms-00ME"
title="Enumerable set">enumerations</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> respectively. Then the function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[e_A\times  e_B\colon  \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}\to  A\times  B]]></fr:tex> can be seen to be <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00M8.xml"
addr="jms-00M8"
title="Surjection">surjective</fr:link>; letting <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> be any enumeration of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>, can compose to obtain a surjection <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (e_A\times  e_B\right )\mathclose {}}\circ  f\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A\times  B]]></fr:tex> by <fr:ref
addr="jms-00MD"
taxon="Theorem" />.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
